sed as the source of another <xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.CroppedBitmap>, chaining the cropping. Note that the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.CroppedBitmap.SourceRect%2A> uses values that are relative to the source cropped bitmap and not the initial image.  \n  \n [!code-xml[imageelementexample#CroppedXAML3](../../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/ImageElementExample/CSharp/CroppedImageExample.xaml#croppedxaml3)]  \n  \n [!code-csharp[imageelementexample#CroppedCSharp2](../../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/ImageElementExample/CSharp/CroppedImageExample.xaml.cs#croppedcsharp2)]\n [!code-vb[imageelementexample#CroppedCSharp2](../../../../samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_Wpf/ImageElementExample/VB/CroppedImageExample.xaml.vb#croppedcsharp2)]  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Create a Clip Region](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/56e4bed6-78d7-4292-b917-d72d0b3e4376)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,50],"content":"How to: Crop an Image | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Crop an Image | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,38]}]},{"pos":[480,501],"content":"How to: Crop an Image","linkify":"How to: Crop an Image","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Crop an Image","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"This example shows how to crop an image using <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.CroppedBitmap&gt;</ph>.","pos":[502,598],"source":"This example shows how to crop an image using <xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.CroppedBitmap>."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.CroppedBitmap&gt;</ph> is primarily used when encoding a cropped version of an image to save out to a file.","pos":[605,739],"source":"<xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.CroppedBitmap> is primarily used when encoding a cropped version of an image to save out to a file."},{"content":"To crop an image for display purposes see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a Clip Region<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/56e4bed6-